“Turn to my reproof,
Behold, I will pour out my spirit on you;
I will make my words known to you.

Do not let lovingkindness and truth forsake you;
Bind them around your neck,
Write them on the tablet of your heart.

Then he instructed me and said to me,
“Let your heart hold fast my words;
Keep my commandments and live

As a loving hind and a graceful doe,
Let her breasts satisfy you at all times;
Be intoxicated always with her love.

Do this then, my son, and deliver yourself;
Since you have come into the hand of your neighbor,
Go, humble yourself, and badger your neighbor.

When you walk about, they will lead you;
When you sleep, they will keep watch over you;
And when you awake, they will speak to you.

Until an arrow pierces through his liver;
As a bird hastens to the snare,
And he does not know that it will cost him his soul.

“The fear of Yahweh is to hate evil;
Pride and arrogance and the evil way
And the mouth of perverted words, I hate.

Then I was beside Him, as a master workman;
And I was a daily delight,
Rejoicing always before Him

All the brothers of a poor man hate him;
How much more do his friends distance themselves from him!
He pursues them with words, but they are no more.

¶Do you see a man skilled in his work?
He will stand before kings;
He will not stand before obscure men.

Know that wisdom is thus for your soul;
If you find it, then there will be a future,
And your hope will not be cut off.

¶Establish your work outside
And make it ready for yourself in the field;
And afterwards, you shall build your house.

And behold, it was completely overgrown with thistles;
Nettles have covered its surface,
And its stone wall has been torn down.

¶Do not go out hastily to plead your case;
Lest, what will you do in the end,
When your neighbor humiliates you?

Do not forsake your friend or your father’s friend,
And do not come to your brother’s house in the day of your disaster;
Better is one who dwells near than a brother far away.

Keep worthlessness and every false word far from me,
Give me neither poverty nor riches;
Feed me with the food that is my portion

For pressing milk brings forth butter,
And pressing the nose brings forth blood;
And pressing anger brings forth strife.
